
	libthreadar is provides C++ classes for
	manipulating threads easily and propagating
	back exception from thread to parent thread

	libthreadar relies on posix thread which and
	does not require C++11 support from the compiler

	libthreadar has been setup from code initially
	part of webdar and also to be used by dar and
	libdar, where from its name.

	It is a simple implementation for simple things
	but as it may be of interest to any other C++ project
	it has been released under the Lesser GPL.

	For details about this license see the
	COPYING and COPYING.LESSER files.
